This is just PoC and rather toy tool:

./prep-srpm --config   config/copr.conf \
            --module   praiskup/ping/quick-package \
            --revision 5ce6ec838e22df0c5dfbb3ca042347a04829f5c1

We heavily depend on `rpkg` for working with `dist-git`.  You can use `rpkg`
directly like:

    # generic options
    set -- --config config/copr.conf

    # anonymous clone only for now
    rpkg "$@" clone -a praiskup/ping/quick-package

    # checkout proper branch
    cd quick-package && git checkout master

    # download sources
    rpkg "$@" --module-name "praiskup/ping/quick-package" sources

Dependencies:
    - crudiny

(motivation https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1410403)
